codex
A couple of the findings share one design issue: the current event model is slot/spawn-oriented, while the strongest journal contract is transition-oriented. I’m going to make that explicit in the proposals instead of pretending every mismatch is a one-line implementation patch.
codex
I’ve got enough context to write the proposal. The main recommendation pattern will be: implementation fixes for concrete runtime bugs and coverage gaps, spec fixes for ambiguous/stale text, and `update-both` where the spec’s own event shape cannot express the behavior it requires.
